annotationA: Toll-9, isoform A; Toll-9 is a transmembrane signalling receptor belonging to the Toll family of protein
annotationB: Spatzle is a secreted protein which, after cleavage by an extracellular serine protease (ea or SPE), can induce the dimerization of Tl, and the subsequent activation of the Toll pathway. It contributes to function of the Toll signaling cascade, which plays a key role in various developmental and immune processes, notably embryonic dorso-ventral patterning and regulation of antimicrobial peptides
